rties in the government. The author investigates the nature of social and political temporality and develops a theoretical framework that allows him to apply his conclusions not only to Poland but also to other formerly communist countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aGroup identityzPoland. 0aPost-communismzPoland. 0aSocial psychologyzPoland. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aKoczanowicz, Leszek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZembrzuska, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745045640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857450456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857450456/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK